<section>
  <h2 id="full-stack-web-development">Full Stack Web Development</h2>

  <p>This course is <strong>a practical</strong>, <strong>hands-on</strong> <strong>introduction</strong> to creating <strong>modern(ish) web applications</strong>. We&#39;ll cover (roughly in this order):</p>

  <ol>
    <li class="fragment">JavaScript (just learning the language itself)</li>
    <li class="fragment">Server Side Programming</li>
    <li class="fragment">Storing Data</li>
    <li class="fragment">Client Side <em>Build-Out</em> (HTML and CSS)</li>
    <li class="fragment">Client Side Programming</li>
    <li class="fragment">A Few <em>Trendy</em> Frameworks / Libraries</li>
    <li class="fragment">And We&#39;ll Pick up Some Development Tools Along the Way *</li>
  </ol>

  <p class="fragment"><br />
Let&#39;s check out the rough <a href="../../schedule.html">schedule on the course site</a></p>
</section>

